    • openSignEditor

      void openSignEditor(org.bukkit.entity.Player player, String[] lines, org.bukkit.Material type, org.bukkit.DyeColor color, org.bukkit.Location signLoc, BiFunction<org.bukkit.entity.Player,String[],String[]> function) throws Exception
      Called when a sign gui should be opened.
      Parameters:
      player - The player to whom the sign is to be shown.
      lines - The lines that are shown.
      type - The type of the sign.
      color - The color of the sign (1.14+)
      signLoc - The location where the sign should be placed. Can be null for default. See getLocation(org.bukkit.entity.Player, int)
      function - The BiFunction which is executed when the editing is finished. If new lines are returned, the new lines are opened to edit.
      Throws:
      Exception
